Business Brief -- Kaufman  Broad Home Corp.:
   New Class of Stock Is Sold
   In Pact With Ex-Parent
The shares will be issued upon exercise of warrants held
by a subsidiary of Broad Inc., Kaufman  Broad's former
parent. The warrants, exercisable at $6.96 a share, were
issued by Kaufman  Broad in connection with the company's
spinoff from Broad in 1989.
   Kaufman  Broad said it won't receive any proceeds
directly from the stock sale, but will receive about $34.8
million from exercise of the warrants. The subsidiary, Sun
Life Insurance Co., will receive gross proceeds equal to the
difference between the stock sale proceeds and the warrants
payment.